Wright Hits Home Run as Mets Beat Phillies 7-4, Snap 5-Game Losing Streak

-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 
2011-08-24T20:56:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/wright-hits-home-run-as-mets-beat-phillies-7-4-snap-5-game-losing-streak.html
David Wright  had three hits,
including a home run, as the  New York Mets  beat the Philadelphia
Phillies 7-4 today, snapping a five-game losing streak and
avoiding a three-game series sweep.  Wright, 28, was 3-for-4 with his 11th of the season and two
runs batted in as the Mets won for the first time since Aug. 17.
Nick Evans added three hits and drove in four runs in the 3-
hour, 41-minute game at Philadelphiaâ€™s Citizens Bank Park.  The Mets scored four runs in the first inning off Kyle Kendrick and added runs in the third, fourth and fifth innings.
New York starter  Mike Pelfrey  allowed nine hits and three runs
over six innings, and won his first game in four weeks.  The Mets were outscored 23-11 in the series by the National
League East division-leading Phillies. New York is 61-68, 22 1/2
games out of first place.  To contact the reporter on this story:
